value.title: Advisers made last-minute push to get reluctant Trump to Walter Reed
value.excerpt: Marine One was idling on the South Lawn Friday as President Donald Trump's advisers were inside the White House making a last-minute push to get him to board the helicopter.

value.title: Trump took photos, had roundtable with donors at Bedminster fundraiser hours before announcing Covid diagnosis
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's big-dollar fundraiser at his New Jersey golf club went on as planned Thursday night despite the President and staff knowing he had been exposed to coronavirus.

value.title: Trump has been 'fever-free' for over 24 hours, hasn't need supplemental oxygen at hospital
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has been fever-free for over 24 hours and has not needed supplemental oxygen Saturday morning, his doctors told reporters outside Walter Reed National Military Medical Center.

value.title: Twitter bans posts wishing for Trump death. The Squad wonders where that policy was for them
value.excerpt: The four progressive Democratic congresswomen known as "The Squad" expressed surprise on Friday night when Twitter posted about its policy against wishing harm or death to someone in light of President Trump's Covid-19 diagnosis.

value.title: Pence tests negative and continues campaigning despite Trump diagnosis
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence tested negative for Covid-19 again, an administration official said Saturday morning, after traveling to multiple states for indoor and outdoor events, participating in numerous White House events and meetings and having been in frequent close contact with President Donald Trump

value.title: There will be more space between Pence and Harris at next week's debate
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and Democratic vice presidential nominee Kamala Harris will be separated by 12 feet at their debate on Wednesday, a source familiar with the plans tells CNN.

value.title: Trump administration puts up billboards of immigration violators in Pennsylvania
value.excerpt: The Trump administration has put up billboards in Pennsylvania of immigration violators, an unprecedented move taken in a swing state a month before the presidential election.

value.title: 'This was avoidable': Trump has been downplaying the virus from the start
value.excerpt: In recent weeks, Trump has put himself and others at risk by holding mass gatherings, some indoors, and shunning mask use while claiming the end of the virus was just around the corner.

value.title: Melania Trump announces she has 'mild symptoms' of coronavirus
value.excerpt: First lady Melania Trump said Friday that she is experiencing "mild symptoms" but is "looking forward to a speedy recovery" following her Covid-19 diagnosis.

value.title: ‘If He Doesn’t Win Ohio, It’s Over’: Trump Slips in the Heartland
value.excerpt: Four years ago, the president easily won Ohio by building a balanced coalition among white voters across educational lines. But his support has waned since then, particularly in the suburbs.

value.title: Pete Wilson endorses Trump, says president has 'very good judgment'
value.excerpt: Wilson was among nearly seven dozen members of past GOP administrations and Congress who backed Trump in a signed letter.

value.title: Trump says he'll overturn 'ridiculous' gender-neutral Navy terms
value.excerpt: The Navy had made the changes to the two elite units' ethos and creed because the terms were outdated and because of the potential for women to join the units.

value.title: Leader of Proud Boys also leads grassroots group Latinos for Trump
value.excerpt: The leader of the Proud Boys, a far-right group thrust into the spotlight earlier this week during the presidential debate, is also the leader of the grassroots group Latinos for Trump.

value.title: McMaster sees Trump 'aiding and abetting' Russia's election efforts
value.excerpt: Former White House National Security Adviser H.R. McMaster has been careful not to criticize Donald Trump. That's just now starting to change.

value.title: Former commander of US forces in Afghanistan endorses Biden
value.excerpt: It's striking how many retired military leaders, many of whom have been apolitical for decades, have stepped up to denounce Trump, endorse Biden, or both.

value.title: Three-quarters of LGBTQ voters back Joe Biden, GLAAD poll finds
value.excerpt: With the presidential election just a month away, 75 percent of LGBTQ voters said they support Biden, while 17 percent back Trump, according to a GLAAD poll.

value.title: Trump signs spending bill to keep government open until December 11
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump early Thursday morning signed a spending bill to keep the government open until December 11, according to a tweet from White House spokesman Judd Deere.

value.title: Federal judge refuses to stop mail-in voting in Montana, blasts Trump-backed 'fiction' of massive voter fraud
value.excerpt: A federal judge in Montana rejected the Trump campaign's effort to stop an expansion of mail-in voting in the state.

value.title: Why did Trump's Intel chief launch a dubious pre-debate gambit?
value.excerpt: The disclosure from DNI was quickly overshadowed by last night's debate, but even by 2020 standards, this was extraordinary.

value.title: Trump's Proud Boys 'stand back and stand by' debate moment was more than a dog whistle
value.excerpt: There are not two sides to white supremacy, just as there are not two sides to homophobia, anti-Semitism or any other type of hate. That is, apparently, unless your name is Donald J. Trump.

value.title: Undecided voters call Trump ‘unhinged’ and ‘un-American’ — but unswayed by debate
value.excerpt: After watching the first presidential debate Tuesday night, undecided voters from battleground states across the country still had plenty they wanted to know about coronavirus, racial injustice and what each candidate would do to unite the country.

value.title: Biden: 'He's the racist'
value.excerpt: During the first presidential debate, President Donald Trump claimed he ended racial sensitivity training because it was "racist" and Joe Biden responded that Trump is the racist.

value.title: Biden paid nearly $300,000 in federal income taxes in 2019
value.excerpt: Joe Biden released his 2019 tax returns on Tuesday, which show he and his wife, Jill, paid nearly $300,000 in federal income tax last year and had an adjusted gross income of about $985,000.

value.title: 'Deeply unpatriotic': Mary Trump slams the president for not paying taxes for years
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's niece, Mary Trump, say the topic of her uncle not paying income taxes for 10 of the last 15 years must be “hammered on” during the first general election debate Tuesday night.

value.title: Does Trump's 'tightening financial vise' create a security risk?
value.excerpt: Trump holding onto power might be one of the few options he has remaining to prevent his creditors from seizing his personal assets.

value.title: Trump's Supreme Court pick on Capitol Hill for meeting with GOP senators
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's nominee for the Supreme Court, Judge Amy Coney Barrett, will meet Republican senators throughout Tuesday on Capitol Hill, as the party finalizes plans for a quick confirmation process ahead of the November presidential election.

value.title: Trump administration warns Iraq it plans to shut U.S. Embassy in Baghdad after rocket attacks
value.excerpt: In an interview with NBC News, a top U.S. general recently praised the work of Iraqi security forces protecting American interests in Iraq.

value.title: Pence tells Americans to 'anticipate that cases will rise' with more coronavirus testing
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence said that "the American people should anticipate that cases will rise" as efforts for increased coronavirus testing are implemented and states in the Midwest are experiencing a surge.

value.title: End the Filibuster? Pack the Court? The Left Is Pushing Biden
value.excerpt: A party that is increasingly seeking to play by different rules is led by a figure who helped create the current ones. The outcome of the fight will help define the Democratic Party going forward.

value.title: ‘Fox & Friends,’ With Donald Trump Jr., Tries to Dismiss Times Tax Article
value.excerpt: The Fox News morning show, a reliable forum for the president and his defenders, serves up criticism of the report and attacks on Joe Biden.
